</td>
<td class="mbox-text" style="">The plot summary in this article <b>is too long or detailed compared to the rest of the content</b>. Please <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=The_Count_of_Monte_Cristo&amp;action=edit" class="external text" title="http://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=The_Count_of_Monte_Cristo&amp;action=edit" rel="nofollow">edit the article</a> to <a href="/wiki/Wikipedia:Manual_of_Style_(writing_about_fiction)" title="Wikipedia:Manual of Style (writing about fiction)">focus on discussing the work</a> rather than merely <a href="/wiki/Wikipedia:What_Wikipedia_is_not#Wikipedia_is_not_an_indiscriminate_collection_of_information" title="Wikipedia:What Wikipedia is not">reiterating the plot</a>. <small><i>(April 2008)</i></small></td>
